Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Loughnan Glossary
Author: LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page: 55
Edition:
Quote: needlegrass: an exotic grass (Stipa variabilis) accidentally introduced, with a tiny, hard, barbed head which penetrates in hundreds through the pelts of sheep and deep into the flesh of their briskets.
